The paper introduces an agent that uses demonstrations to solve exploration problems in partially observable environments, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of reinforcement learning and deep learning techniques, which are commonly associated with machine learning (cs.LG). The agent is designed to operate in highly variable initial conditions, which suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper introduces a suite of tasks that involve visual perception, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV).
